GAP-3 (#1109): a structural `>>` search windows the L (seed) and R leaf scans,
AND the recursive closure's bare `t`-scan. That `t`-scan is emitter-synthetic
(not a chplan leaf), so the leaf-window pass cannot reach it; it is stamped
directly by windowRecursiveScans, which lands a bare `Timestamp >= ... AND <= ...`
conjunct on the physical `otel_traces` scan inside the recursive arm. This is the
partition prune the inert `t.TraceId IN (<seed>)` membership can never deliver:
only a Timestamp predicate sitting on the scan prunes the toDate(Timestamp)
partitions, so without it the closure re-scans full retention (the GAP-3 OOM).
Tradeoff (accepted): windowing `t` drops off-window connective spans, so a chain
whose intermediate hops straddle the window edge degrades to a partial closure —
the same residual the seed-trace-id top-N already accepts (kept traces sit in
the window).

Memory bound (Bug 2 / structural-closure top-N): with a `search_limit`, every
structural leaf (the L seed, the step's `_seed_ids` re-render, and the R scan)
also carries `TraceId IN (SELECT TraceId FROM otel_traces WHERE ParentSpanId=''
... GROUP BY TraceId ORDER BY min(Timestamp) DESC, TraceId LIMIT 20)` — the SAME
top-N-newest-root BoundedTraceScope gate the nested-set structure-tab path uses
(boundedRootScopeFrag). The scan was already windowed (the GAP-3 fix above), but
the closure seed still ran over EVERY in-window trace and only truncated to N
afterward, peaking the WITH RECURSIVE working set past the per-query memory cap
(prod `{} >> {}` read ~525K rows and OOM'd). The gate restricts the closure seed
to the N requested traces, matching the nested-set path's ranking so the two
search paths keep the same traces. stampStructuralTraceLimit pushes it.

-- search_limit --
20
-- search_window --
1782571392 1782573192
-- query.traceql --
{ resource.service.name = "a" } >> { span.http.status_code = 500 }
-- sql --
SELECT R.`TraceId` AS `TraceId`, R.`SpanId` AS `SpanId`, R.`ParentSpanId` AS `ParentSpanId`, R.`SpanName` AS `SpanName`, R.`Duration` AS `Duration`, R.`Timestamp` AS `Timestamp`, R.`ResourceAttributes` AS `ResourceAttributes`, R.`SpanAttributes` AS `SpanAttributes`, R.`StatusCode` AS `StatusCode`, R.`StatusMessage` AS `StatusMessage`, R.`SpanKind` AS `SpanKind`, R.`ScopeName` AS `ScopeName`, R.`ScopeVersion` AS `ScopeVersion` FROM (WITH RECURSIVE _struct_closure_1 AS (SELECT DISTINCT `TraceId`, `SpanId`, `ParentSpanId`, 0 AS _depth FROM (SELECT * FROM `otel_traces` WHERE (`Timestamp` >= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(?)) AND (`Timestamp` <= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(?)) AND (`ResourceAttributes`[?] = ?)) AS _seed UNION ALL SELECT DISTINCT t.`TraceId`, t.`SpanId`, t.`ParentSpanId`, c._depth + 1 FROM `otel_traces` AS t INNER JOIN _struct_closure_1 AS c ON t.`TraceId` = c.`TraceId` AND t.`ParentSpanId` = c.`SpanId` WHERE c._depth < 128 AND t.`TraceId` IN (SELECT `TraceId` FROM (SELECT * FROM `otel_traces` WHERE (`Timestamp` >= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(?)) AND (`Timestamp` <= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(?)) AND (`ResourceAttributes`[?] = ?)) AS _seed_ids) AND `Timestamp` >= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(1782571392000000000) AND `Timestamp` <= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(1782573192000000000)) SELECT DISTINCT `TraceId`, `SpanId` FROM _struct_closure_1 WHERE _depth > 0) AS L INNER JOIN (SELECT * FROM `otel_traces` WHERE (`Timestamp` >= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(?)) AND (`Timestamp` <= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(?)) AND (toFloat64OrNull(`SpanAttributes`[?]) = ?)) AS R ON L.`TraceId` = R.`TraceId` AND L.`SpanId` = R.`SpanId`
-- args --
[0] int64 = 1782571392000000000
[1] int64 = 1782573192000000000
[2] string = "service.name"
[3] string = "a"
[4] int64 = 1782571392000000000
[5] int64 = 1782573192000000000
[6] string = "service.name"
[7] string = "a"
[8] int64 = 1782571392000000000
[9] int64 = 1782573192000000000
[10] string = "http.status_code"
[11] int64 = 500
-- chplan --
StructuralJoin op=>> maxDepth=128
  Filter predicate=((ResourceAttributes["service.name"] = "a") AND ((Timestamp >= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(1782571392000000000)) AND (Timestamp <= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(1782573192000000000))))
    Scan(otel_traces)
  Filter predicate=((toFloat64OrNull(SpanAttributes["http.status_code"]) = 500) AND ((Timestamp >= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(1782571392000000000)) AND (Timestamp <= fromUnixTimestamp64Nano(1782573192000000000))))
    Scan(otel_traces)
